description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and dedicated Occupational Therapist to work within the High Peak and North Dales Older Adult Community Mental Health Teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Occupational Therapist is part of a multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The OT approach will consider therapeutic, meaningful activities to support individual&#39;s recovery and wellbeing in mental health within the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will have the OT skills and knowledge to provide specialist functional assessments and be committed to providing high-quality, person-centred care. &lt;span&gt;Knowledge of organic and functional illnesses is essential in this role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a suitably experienced Occupational Therapist who is motivated and dedicated, to work within the current team, to contribute to the continued development and promotion of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is anticipated that this will be achieved through MDT work, representing the team within the Trust and an ability to provide a positive role model to other team members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will carry a clinical caseload of people experiencing a wide range of moderate, to severe, mental illness, facilitate group work, liaise with community partners to promote a person-centred approach to care and support the team with their clinical work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return, you can expect to be supported in your professional development, develop skills appropriate to the needs of the service and client group and be part of a fantastic team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Car driver essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joanne Hanby, Service Manager, joannehanby@nhs.net, 0300 123 3373&lt;/p&gt;
